derivation.yuyuan_name: mid 19th cent. (originally US): variant of dialect feeze 'drive or frighten off', from Old English fēsian, of unknown origin

entry.tran: 使胆怯;使惊呆;使惊慌失措
entry.def: If something fazes you, it surprises, shocks, or frightens you, so that you do not know what to do.
